<br>[学习本文需要基础词汇量：<x-rating>8</x-rating>,000 ]<br>[本次分析采用基础词汇量：<x-rating2>4</x-rating2>,000 ]<br><p style="line-height: 150%">箴16:1 <br>The preparations of the heart in man, and the answer of the tongue, is from the LORD.<br>心中的谋算在乎人；舌头的应对由于耶和华。<br><br><br>箴16:2 <br>All the ways of a man are clean in his own eyes; but the LORD weigheth the spirits.<br>人一切所行的，在自己眼中看为清洁，惟有耶和华衡量人心。<br><br><br>箴16:3 <br>Commit <x-word word="thy"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">thy</span></x-word> works <x-word word="unto"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">unto</span></x-word> the LORD, and <x-word word="thy"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">thy</span></x-word> thoughts shall be established.<br>你所做的，要交托耶和华，你所谋的，就必成立。<br><br><br>箴16:4 <br>The LORD <x-word word="hath"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">hath</span></x-word> made all things for himself: <x-word word="yea"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #800000;">yea</span></x-word>, even the <x-word word="wicked"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">wicked</span></x-word> for the day of evil.<br>耶和华所造的，各适其用，就是恶人，也为祸患的日子所造。<br><br><br>箴16:5 <br>Every one that is proud in heart is an <x-word word="abomination"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #800000;">abomination</span></x-word> to the LORD: though hand join in hand, he shall not be <x-word word="unpunished"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #800000;">unpunished</span></x-word>.<br>凡心里骄傲的，为耶和华所憎恶，虽然连手，他必不免受罚。<br><br><br>箴16:6 <br>By <x-word word="mercy"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">mercy</span></x-word> and truth <x-word word="iniquity"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #800000;">iniquity</span></x-word> is <x-word word="purged"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">purged</span></x-word>: and by the fear of the LORD men <x-group group="departXfrom"><span style="box-shadow: 0px 3px white, 0px 4px #00BFFF;"><x-word word="depart"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">depart</span></x-word> from</span></x-group> evil.<br>因怜悯诚实，罪孽得赎；敬畏耶和华的，远离恶事。<br><br><br>箴16:7 <br>When a man's ways please the LORD, he maketh even his enemies to be at peace with him.<br>人所行的，若蒙耶和华喜悦，耶和华也使他的仇敌与他和好。<br><br><br>箴16:8 <br>Better is a little with <x-word word="righteousness"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #800000;">righteousness</span></x-word> than great revenues without right.<br>多有财利，行事不义，不如少有财利，行事公义。<br><br><br>箴16:9 <br>A man's heart <x-word word="deviseth"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #0000FF;">deviseth</span></x-word> his way: but the LORD <x-word word="directeth"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #0000FF;">directeth</span></x-word> his steps.<br>人心筹算自己的道路，惟耶和华指引他的脚步。<br><br><br>箴16:10 <br>A <x-word word="divine"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">divine</span></x-word> sentence is in the lips of the king: his mouth <x-word word="transgresseth"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #0000FF;">transgresseth</span></x-word> not in judgment.<br>王的嘴中有 神语，审判之时，他的口必不差错。<br><br><br>箴16:11 <br>A just weight and balance are the LORD's: all the weights of the bag are his work.<br>公道的天平和秤都属耶和华；囊中一切法码都为他所定。<br><br><br>箴16:12 <br>It is an <x-word word="abomination"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #800000;">abomination</span></x-word> to kings to commit <x-word word="wickedness"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #800000;">wickedness</span></x-word>: for <x-group group="theXthrone"><span style="box-shadow: 0px 3px white, 0px 4px #00BFFF;">the <x-word word="throne"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">throne</span></x-word></span></x-group> is established by <x-word word="righteousness"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #800000;">righteousness</span></x-word>.<br>作恶，为王所憎恶，因国位是靠公义坚立。<br><br><br>箴16:13 <br><x-word word="righteous"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">Righteous</span></x-word> lips are the delight of kings; and they love him that <x-word word="speaketh"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #0000FF;">speaketh</span></x-word> right.<br>公义的嘴，为王所喜悦；说正直话的，为王所喜爱。<br><br><br>箴16:14 <br>The <x-word word="wrath"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">wrath</span></x-word> of a king is as <x-word word="messengers"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">messengers</span></x-word> of death: but <x-group group="aXwiseXman"><span style="box-shadow: 0px 3px white, 0px 4px #00BFFF;">a wise man</span></x-group> will <x-word word="pacify"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #800000;">pacify</span></x-word> it.<br>王的震怒如杀人的使者，但智慧人能止息王怒。<br><br><br>箴16:15 <br>In the light of the king's <x-word word="countenance"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #800000;">countenance</span></x-word> is life; and his favour is as a cloud of the latter rain.<br>王的脸光使人有生命；王的恩典好像春云时雨。<br><br><br>箴16:16 <br>How much better is it to get wisdom than gold! and to get understanding rather to be chosen than silver!<br>得智慧胜似得金子；选聪明强如选银子。<br><br><br>箴16:17 <br>The highway of the <x-word word="upright"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">upright</span></x-word> is to <x-group group="departXfrom"><span style="box-shadow: 0px 3px white, 0px 4px #00BFFF;"><x-word word="depart"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">depart</span></x-word> from</span></x-group> evil: he that <x-word word="keepeth"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #0000FF;">keepeth</span></x-word> his way <x-word word="preserveth"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #0000FF;">preserveth</span></x-word> his soul.<br>正直人的道，是远离恶事；谨守己路的，是保全性命。<br><br><br>箴16:18 <br>Pride <x-word word="goeth"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #0000FF;">goeth</span></x-word> before destruction, and an <x-word word="haughty"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #800000;">haughty</span></x-word> spirit before a fall.<br>骄傲在败坏以先；狂心在跌倒之前。<br><br><br>箴16:19 <br>Better it is to be of an <x-word word="humble"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">humble</span></x-word> spirit with the <x-word word="lowly"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">lowly</span></x-word>, than to divide the <x-group group="spoilXwith"><span style="box-shadow: 0px 3px white, 0px 4px #00BFFF;"><x-word word="spoil"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">spoil</span></x-word> with</span></x-group> the proud.<br>心里谦卑与穷乏人来往，强如将掳物与骄傲人同分。<br><br><br>箴16:20 <br>He that <x-word word="handleth"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #0000FF;">handleth</span></x-word> a matter <x-word word="wisely"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">wisely</span></x-word> shall find good: and <x-word word="whoso"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #0000FF;">whoso</span></x-word> <x-word word="trusteth"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #0000FF;">trusteth</span></x-word> in the LORD, happy is he.<br>谨守训言的，必得好处；倚靠耶和华的，便为有福！<br><br><br>箴16:21 <br><x-group group="theXwise"><span style="box-shadow: 0px 3px white, 0px 4px #00BFFF;">The wise</span></x-group> in heart shall be called <x-word word="prudent"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">prudent</span></x-word>: and the <x-word word="sweetness"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">sweetness</span></x-word> of the lips <x-word word="increaseth"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #0000FF;">increaseth</span></x-word> learning.<br>心中有智慧，必称为通达人；嘴中的甜言，加增人的学问。<br><br><br>箴16:22 <br>Understanding is a <x-word word="wellspring"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #800000;">wellspring</span></x-word> of life <x-word word="unto"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">unto</span></x-word> him that <x-word word="hath"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">hath</span></x-word> it: but the instruction of fools is <x-word word="folly"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">folly</span></x-word>.<br>人有智慧就有生命的泉源；愚昧人必被愚昧惩治。<br><br><br>箴16:23 <br>The heart of <x-group group="theXwise"><span style="box-shadow: 0px 3px white, 0px 4px #00BFFF;">the wise</span></x-group> <x-word word="teacheth"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #0000FF;">teacheth</span></x-word> his mouth, and <x-word word="addeth"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #0000FF;">addeth</span></x-word> learning to his lips.<br>智慧人的心教训他的口，又使他的嘴增长学问。<br><br><br>箴16:24 <br>Pleasant words are as an <x-word word="honeycomb"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #800000;">honeycomb</span></x-word>, sweet to the soul, and health to the bones.<br>良言如同蜂房，使心觉甘甜，使骨得医治。<br><br><br>箴16:25 <br>There is a way that <x-word word="seemeth"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #0000FF;">seemeth</span></x-word> right <x-word word="unto"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">unto</span></x-word> a man, but the end <x-word word="thereof"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">thereof</span></x-word> are the ways of death.<br>有一条路，人以为正，至终成为死亡之路。<br><br><br>箴16:26 <br>He that laboureth laboureth for himself; for his mouth craveth it of him.<br>劳力人的胃口，使他劳力，因为他的口腹催逼他。<br><br><br>箴16:27 <br>An <x-word word="ungodly"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #800000;">ungodly</span></x-word> man diggeth up evil: and in his lips there is as a burning fire.<br>匪徒图谋奸恶，嘴上仿佛有烧焦的火。<br><br><br>箴16:28 <br>A <x-word word="froward"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #0000FF;">froward</span></x-word> man <x-word word="soweth"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #0000FF;">soweth</span></x-word> <x-word word="strife"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">strife</span></x-word>: and a <x-word word="whisperer"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #800000;">whisperer</span></x-word> <x-word word="separateth"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #0000FF;">separateth</span></x-word> chief friends.<br>乖僻人播散纷争；传舌的离间密友。<br><br><br>箴16:29 <br>A violent man <x-word word="enticeth"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #0000FF;">enticeth</span></x-word> his neighbour, and <x-word word="leadeth"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #0000FF;">leadeth</span></x-word> him into the way that is not good.<br>强暴人诱惑邻舍，领他走不善之道。<br><br><br>箴16:30 <br>He <x-word word="shutteth"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #0000FF;">shutteth</span></x-word> his eyes to devise <x-word word="froward"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #0000FF;">froward</span></x-word> things: moving his lips he <x-word word="bringeth"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #0000FF;">bringeth</span></x-word> evil to pass.<br>眼目紧合的，图谋乖僻；嘴唇紧闭的，成就邪恶。<br><br><br>箴16:31 <br>The <x-word word="hoary"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #800000;">hoary</span></x-word> head is a crown of glory, if it be found in the way of <x-word word="righteousness"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #800000;">righteousness</span></x-word>.<br>白发是荣耀的冠冕，在公义的道上，必能得着。<br><br><br>箴16:32 <br>He that is slow to anger is better than the <x-word word="mighty"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">mighty</span></x-word>; and he that <x-word word="ruleth"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #0000FF;">ruleth</span></x-word> his spirit than he that <x-word word="taketh"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #0000FF;">taketh</span></x-word> a city.<br>不轻易发怒的，胜过勇士；治服己心的，强如取城。<br><br><br>箴16:33 <br>The lot is cast into the lap; but the whole <x-word word="disposing"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">disposing</span></x-word> <x-word word="thereof"><span style="border-bottom:1px solid #FF0000;">thereof</span></x-word> is of the LORD.<br>签放在怀里，定事由耶和华。</p>

